# ---------------
45. Numeric types
# ---------------

Golang spec --> Numeric types

int & uint -- implementation-specific sizes

byte is an alias for uint8
rune is an alias for int32

int32 and int are not the same!!

Rule of thumb:
	Just use "int"
	just use "float64"

runtime package:
	GOOS, GOARCH
code: https://play.golang.org/p/1vp5DImIMM


